✅ Jenkins Plugin Installation (UI Method)
Login to Jenkins.

Go to Manage Jenkins → Plugins (or "Manage Plugins").

Go to the Available tab.

In the search box, type the plugin name (e.g., Matrix Authorization Strategy).

✅ Check the box next to the plugin.

Click Install without restart (or Download now and install after restart).

Wait for installation to finish.

🔁 After Install (if needed)
Go to Manage Jenkins → Configure Global Security to configure plugin settings (e.g., user roles for Matrix plugin).

💡 Example Plugin Names to Install
Plugin Name	Purpose
Matrix Authorization Strategy	Manage users/roles
GitHub Plugin	Integrate GitHub
Pipeline	For Jenkins pipelines
Docker Pipeline	Build using Docker
